All parties backed a resolution by African National Congress (ANC) Chief Whip Jackson Mthembu a short while ago. CAPE TOWN Parliament s inquiry into the funding of political parties is officially underway.The National Assembly has agreed to the formation of a multi-party ad hoc committee to look into the matter.All parties backed a resolution by African National Congress (ANC) Chief Whip Jackson Mthembu a short while ago.The inquiry will investigate whether public funding of political parties is adequate, but will also consider the need to regulate private funding, including its disclosure. Investment arms of political parties, such as the ANC s Chancellor House, will also come under scrutiny.Mthembu says parties need enough funding to do their jobs and to enhance democracy. The manner and transparency of such funding is paramount in the context of building public confidence in the political system. The 11 member committee will have six MPs from the ANC, two from the DA, one from the EFF and two representing the other parties.It must report back to the National Assembly by 30 November 2017.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)